latestIgtvVideos.title: Cottonians Connect Virtual Event
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Dear Cottonians’
We are a day away from hosting the "" and will feature Siddharth Rajsekar (ICSE Class of 1999, Elphick House), scheduled on the 23rd January 2021, at 8PM IST.
In this 60-minute keynote, Sidz will give members a crash course in digital marketing and will help them understand which buttons they need to push to activate their digital presence effectively. This will be very impactful especially for existing entrepreneurs who are feeling stuck and not having the marketing power.
To register to the "Cottonians Connect Virtual Event" please visit our events page on the website: https://www.thecottonians.com/events
Link in the bio 📝

latestPosts.caption:
🌟 Join Us for a Special Evening! Forever Green & Gold: Retro Rhythms Concert 🌟

📅 Date: June 21st, 2025 (Saturday) | Time: 5:00 PM - 6:30 PM
📍 Venue: Mother Tekla Auditorium, Brunton Road, Bangalore
🕓 Meet & Greet, Tea: 4PM - 5PM
🎟️ Tickets: Rs. 499/- onwards, available on BookMyShow 
 🔗Link in the bio

​An enchanting performance of retro english songs by Rear Admiral Dr. Nirmala Kannan (Retd.)—a distinguished Old Cottonian ​and a woman of many accomplishments as an Indian Naval Officer.
🎖️ Honors: Vishisht Seva Medal (1993), Nau Sena Medal (2012)
🎤 A renowned performer captivating audiences across India and beyond.
Don't miss out—book your tickets now!​ We look forward to seeing you there!

Best Wishes, 
🔰Old Cottonians' Association
Bishop Cotton Girls' School
